Canonical skill playbooks are maintained upstream in the cogmemory repo:

    https://github.com/bketelsen/cogmemory/tree/main/docs/llm/skills/

The *.md files here are vendored copies with ytsejam's HOST-ADAPTATION
points applied (reflect: transcript mining via sessions/--chat--/*.jsonl;
cog: domain skills generated into data/skills with the local write tool).
When updating a playbook, change it upstream first, then re-vendor here
AND sync the live copy in server/data/skills/ (seeding is copy-if-missing,
so editing this seed alone does not update a running instance).

This file has no .md extension on purpose: the skills store seeds and
lists only *.md files.
